		<script>
			var startController = {
					checkInterval: null,
					
				checkCallback: function () {
						window.clearInterval(startController.checkInterval);
						delete startController.checkInterval;
		                
                        if (document.getElementById('extension-is-installed')) {
                            return;
                        }				

						var browsername = startController.getBrowserName().toLowerCase();
						if (browsername == "chrome"){
							$("#errorDiv").show();
							$("#preparingBrowser").hide();
							
							var extensionImg = document.createElement("img");
							extensionImg.setAttribute("src", "chrome-extension://eecodgfbjbfgdhcfideckcjacenogika/images/128.png"); // See below for discussion of how to find this

							extensionImg.addEventListener("load", function(e) {
								$("#installedRecorder").show();
								$("#getRecorder").hide();
							}, false);
							extensionImg.addEventListener("error", function(e) {
								$("#getRecorder").show();
								$("#installedRecorder").hide();
							}, false);
						}
				},
				
				getBrowserName: function () {
					var N = navigator.appName, ua = navigator.userAgent, tem;
					var M = ua.match(/(opera|chrome|safari|firefox|msie)\/?\s*(\.?\d+(\.\d+)*)/i);
					if (M && (tem = ua.match(/version\/([\.\d]+)/i)) != null) M[2] = tem[1];
					M = M ? [M[1], M[2]] : [N, navigator.appVersion, '-?'];

					return M[0];
				},
					
				initialize: function () {

					$(document).ready(function () {
						$("#errorDiv").hide();
					});

					startController.checkInterval = window.setInterval(startController.checkCallback, 5000);
				}
			}

			startController.initialize();
		</script>
